CatDescriptText: Mr. George Deakings, 63 Bates Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think Pennsylvania's 'blue laws' against 'unnecessary' Sunday sales should be enforced?" answer reads: "I think that it should be enforced. It would tidy-up some spots and make the places look better."
